# Component Conventions

## Astro vs React — The Rule

| Use `.astro` for | Use `.tsx` for |
|---|---|
| Static sections, layout, buttons, footer, header | Client-side interactivity: animations, accordion state, mobile menu |

- React islands hydrate with `client:visible` (lazy, preferred) or `client:load` (immediate, only when needed)

## Animation Pattern

All animations use `src/lib/motion.ts` — never define ad hoc variants inline.

```tsx
// Scroll-triggered section reveal
<AnimatedSection client:visible>
  ...
</AnimatedSection>

// Staggered children
<AnimatedSection variant="stagger" client:visible>
  <AnimatedItem>...</AnimatedItem>
  <AnimatedItem>...</AnimatedItem>
</AnimatedSection>

// Hero (dedicated components only)
<HeroContainer> <HeroOverline> <HeroHeadline> <HeroSubhead> <HeroCta>
```

- Every animated component **must** call `useReducedMotion()` and render instantly when true

## Tailwind 4 Reminder

There is no `tailwind.config.js`. All customisation lives in `@theme` inside `src/styles/global.css`. The `@tailwindcss/vite` plugin handles the build.
